<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="b29fd94b-b46b-4c75-8123-750d7d580968" >

    <p>A planned gift is a charitable donation that can be arranged during your lifetime, but will be used by Ryerson in the future. Planned gifts often enable donors to make significant gifts while also fulfilling important tax and financial goals. The most common type of planned gift is a bequest, but there are others, including: charitable remainder trusts, gifts of residual interest, life insurance, and gifts of RRIFs and RRSPs.</p> 
<p>To find out more about planned giving, please <a href="/content/ryerson/giving/giving-for-tomorrow.html">visit our planned giving page</a> or contact:</p> 
<p><strong>Mira Claxton</strong><br> Director of Development, Planned Giving<br> <a href="mailto:mira.claxton@ryerson.ca">mira.claxton@ryerson.ca</a><br> 416.979.5000&nbsp;ext.&nbsp;553793</p>
    





</div>
